SOFTWARE ARCHITECTURE
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

CLASS STRUCTURE (OOP Design)
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

DataLoader
  Responsibility: Data ingestion from Excel
  Methods:
    • load_all_sheets(): Load all worksheets
    • validate_sheet_exists(): Verify required sheets
  Dependencies: pandas, openpyxl

DataValidator
  Responsibility: Schema and quality validation
  Methods:
    • validate_schema(): Check required columns
    • profile_data_quality(): Generate quality report
  Dependencies: pandas

DataCleaner
  Responsibility: Data preparation and cleaning
  Methods:
    • handle_missing_prices(): Impute missing values
    • remove_duplicates(): Remove duplicate records
    • standardize_values(): Normalize text values
    • mask_pii(): Hash sensitive data
    • handle_invalid_quantities(): Remove invalid records
    • standardize_product_names(): Normalize product names
    • clean_full_pipeline(): Orchestrate cleaning
  Dependencies: pandas, hashlib

DataTransformer
  Responsibility: Enrichment and metric creation
  Methods:
    • enrich_with_product_dimension(): Join with product table
    • calculate_business_metrics(): Create calculated fields
  Dependencies: pandas, numpy

KPIAggregator
  Responsibility: KPI calculation and reporting
  Methods:
    • calculate_kpis(): Compute all business metrics
    • print_kpi_summary(): Display formatted output
  Dependencies: pandas

DataExporter
  Responsibility: Output serialization
  Methods:
    • export_to_csv(): Save as CSV
    • export_to_excel(): Save as XLSX
    • export_kpis_to_json(): Save KPIs as JSON
    • export_audit_log(): Save audit trail
  Dependencies: pandas, json, pathlib


EXECUTION FLOW
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

1. Initialize all 6 modules
2. Load data from Excel (DataLoader)
3. Validate schema (DataValidator)
4. Combine datasets (union)
5. Clean data (DataCleaner → multiple steps)
6. Transform and enrich (DataTransformer)
7. Calculate KPIs (KPIAggregator)
8. Export outputs (DataExporter)
9. Log audit trail
10. Return cleaned data + KPIs


ERROR HANDLING & LOGGING
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Logging Strategy
  Level: INFO (major steps)
  Format: [timestamp] [level] [message]
  Output: Console + Log file
  
  Example Output:
  2026-06-01 23:34:25 | INFO     | Loading Excel file: ...
  2026-06-01 23:34:26 | INFO     | Found sheets: ['product_details', ...]
  2026-06-01 23:34:27 | INFO     | Schema validation passed
  2026-06-01 23:34:28 | INFO     | Combining retail datasets...
  2026-06-01 23:34:30 | INFO     | DATA CLEANING PIPELINE STARTING
  2026-06-01 23:34:31 | INFO     | Missing prices handled: 400 rows filled
  2026-06-01 23:34:32 | INFO     | Duplicates removed: 580
  ...
  2026-06-01 23:34:40 | INFO     | PIPELINE EXECUTION COMPLETED SUCCESSFULLY


Exception Handling
  • File not found: ValueError with guidance
  • Missing sheets: ValueError with sheet list
  • Schema validation: ValueError with column names
  • Data type errors: Coerced with pd.to_datetime(errors='coerce')
  • Merge issues: Left join with unmatched reporting
  • Export failures: Caught and logged with path info

Audit Trail
  Tracked Metrics:
  • rows_loaded: Initial row count
  • rows_cleaned: After all cleaning steps
  • rows_exported: Final output count
  • run_timestamp: ISO format datetime
  • pipeline_status: SUCCESS or FAILED


